last_episode_to_air.name: Bent, Battered, Bowed but Never Broken
last_episode_to_air.overview: One thing after another goes wrong for the KLH team as they build a three-car garage for a client. With broken logs, trailers and trucks, the guys scramble for solutions.

name: Lincoln Log Masters
overview: Follow Cody, Wilson, and the only building company in existence with the Lincoln Log stamp of approval, as they design, build, break down and rebuild epic log homes and structures across Oregon facing dangerous and epic weather conditions, unpredictable delays and demanding locations for their team and builds.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Follow Cody, Wilson, and the only building company in existence with the Lincoln Log stamp of approval, as they design, build, break down and rebuild epic log homes and structures across Oregon facing dangerous and epic weather conditions, unpredictable delays and demanding locations for their team and builds.

episodes.name: How to Trap a Beaver With a Cabin
episodes.overview: The “Trapper’s Cabin” is iconic Americana, so when the guys get to build one for a KLH client in Roseburg, only the best will do. That includes adding ‘knaughty’ log extras to this traditional cabin.

episodes.name: We've Got a Log Problem
episodes.overview: Logs keep the KLH team in business, so when supplies dry up Cody and Wilson go on the hunt. Meanwhile, a restoration job in Christmas Valley is the gift that keeps on giving—but not in a good way.

episodes.name: Logs, Man Cave
episodes.overview: When a client orders a man cave with 45-foot beams, finding and installing the large logs is serious business. Workaholic Wilson needs a break, so Cody reels him into going fishing.

episodes.name: A Raptor's Delight
episodes.overview: When a nonprofit needs a sheep barn built for fire prevention, the guys get to building. Meanwhile, Wilson builds a bocce ball court for a high roller client.

episodes.name: The Dark Side of the Mountain
episodes.overview: When an adventure company needs a cabin built at the base of a ski mountain, the KLH team braves frigid conditions, working through the night to avoid the disruption of daytime business operations.

episodes.name: Logs on Wheels
episodes.overview: The team goes back to school when a client wants a school bus retrofitted into a log cabin—Cody and Wilson will need to learn some new tricks to ace this build.

episodes.name: A Real Life Lincoln Log Playground
episodes.overview: When a local daycare needs play structures built, Cody, Wilson and the KLH team get to work creating a life size Lincoln Log playground, complete with a ‘mini’ cabin, swings, a log spin and much more.
